nditionally. FAWU, the Union representative of a great many of the employees of both parties, participated in the proceedings before the Commission. FAWU submitted that the merger should be prohibited on the grounds that it will lead to a reduction in comp
etition and will also have a detrimental effect on public interest. }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s3\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033 
